@NODE "install" "Installation of VCON"

  Installation
  ------------

VCON_inetd:

The installation of VCON works like any other inetd
program, just copy the VCON_inetd  executable somewhere
into your harddrive. Amitcp:serv/ is recomended,
or Miami:serv/.
If you are using Amitcp add the line:
"telnet  stream  tcp  nowait  nobody Amitcp:serv/VCON_inetd VCON"
to the file Amitcp:db/inetd.conf. If you are using Miami, go to
the Database - InetD section, press the Add button and add the
following information: Service: telnet, Socket: stream,
Protocol: tcp, Wait: nowait User: nobody,
Server: Miami:serv/VCON_inetd, Name: VCON You can also specify
the name of the prefsfile. If nothing is entered under args, VCON
will open S:VCON.prefs as default.

VCON_listen:

This is the version that can be used without inetd. Just start
the program and it will wait for a connection, but set some
prefs info first. (Described below)

VCON_device:

This is the version that waits for a connection on a device.
Just start the program and everything will work, but set some
prefs info first. (Described below)

  VCONPrefs
  ---------
  Now it's time to modify the prefs. It can be done using the prefsprogram
or just editing the S:VCON.prefs file by hand. It's recomened to use the
prefsprogram, because VCON will quit if it finds some strange lines in
the prefsfile. THE PREFSFILE FROM VCON 0.3 OR LOWER IS NOT COMPATIBLE
WITH VCON 0.4 OR ABOVE!

After starting VCONPrefs you will find one mainwindow and one little
error requester. This is fully normal :). The errorrequester will only
appear the first time.

In the textfield Prefsfile you can enter which prefs you will use to
save and load settings from. If you enter something else than S:VCON.prefs
you also have to say that to VCON by typing the same filename into the args,
described above.

The prefs program is devided to four groups Network, Logging, Login and
Shutdown. 

First the nerwork section::
The Port textfield is for the listen program and is to set the port to listen
to. The Device and Unit textfields is for the device program. The ConnectScript
is also used for the device program. It's a very simple connectscript and
I recomend you to use some extern program like ipdial if you want to use a
modem with VCON. THe only thing it does is to send 'ATZ\n' and send 'ATA\n'
when recieving 'RING' and continue when 'CONNECT'
.
The next group is Logging and the Window textfiled and button is for
direct logging. It's recomended to type a consolename here, like raw: or
something. The Logdir Textfiled is used to save logfiles into. Every time
VCON starts and LogDir is activated it will create a file called VCON-????.log,
where ???? is a number. It has exactly the same output as the filelog.
The "Close window when  CtrlD is pressed" is used to enable VCON to close the
logwindow when it recieves Ctrl-D and open it the next time
.
Login section:
LoginSystem is used to specify if you want to use multiuser.library
login system or usergroup.library, or no login at all. If you chose to have
nologin, you also have to enter someting in the command textfield. LoginTime
and LoginTries is used to specify how many times and have long time the user will
have to enter its loginname and password before the connection is closed. 
The Commandfrom cyclenbutton is used the tell VCON where to get the Command that
will be executed right after login. CommandFrom-Command means that the Command
will be taken from the textfield Command. CommandFrom-passwdfile means that the
Command will be taken from the passwfile and CommandFrom-passwdfile+1 menas that
the Command will be taken from the passwdfile one step to the right (skipping the
first char). This could be useful if you have a star in every Shellentry in the
passwdfile. The Command textfield is as described the Command when LoginType-
NoLogin or CommandFrom-Command is selected. Allow users cyclebutton is used
to select which users that have acces to telnet on the machine. AllosUsers-
Always means that all users have acces to telnet. AllowUsers-onlyif* means
that users only have acces to telnet if there is a `*` as the first char in
the Shell entry in the passwd file. When AllowUsers-UserFile is selected only
the users that are in the users file have acces to telnet. The Userfile will
contain only one line per user. Like:
S:telnetuses
root
guest
hEksa
The Bannerfile textfield is used send a message to the user before it can
login. 

And finaly the shutdown entry is to tell VCON what to do when the connection is
closed. "Shutdonw when CtrlC is pressed " is used to enable VCON to close the
connection if it recieves Ctrl-C. FirstBreak is the time that VCON will wait to
send breaksignals if the connection is closed and programs are still using VCON.
Continue Break is the time that VCON will wait between each signal. Ctrl-C and
Ctrl-D is the signals that VCON will send.

I don't think I will have to explain the Save, Load and Quit buttons.

  Prefsfile
  ---------

If you want to edit the prefsfile by hand the args you can use are these:

WinLogFile/K,WinLogFlag/K,DirLogDir/K,DirLogFlag/K,LoginType/K,Command/K,BannerFile/K,
BannerFlag/K,LoginTries/N/K,LoginTime/N/K,Port/K,Device/K,Unit/N/K,Script/K,CloseWin/K,
CloseC/K,FirstBreak/N/K,ContBreak/N/K,BreakC/K,BreakD/K,CmdFrom/K,Allow/K,UserFile/K"

WinLogFile/K is the logfile.
WinLogFlag/K can be ON or OFF an tells VCON if it will open the WinLigFile
DirLogDir/K is the logdrawer.
DirLogFlag/K can be ON or OFF an tells VCON if it will open then DirLogDir
LoginType/K can be one of MULTIUSER, USERGROUP or NOLOGIN.
Command/K is the startup command.
BannerFile/K is the startup message file.
BannerFile/K can be ON or OFF and tells VCON if it will open the BannerFile
LoginTries/N/K and LoginTime/N/K is tries and times to login. If =0 then no limit.
Port/K is the port for the listen program.
Device/K is the device for the device program.
Unit/N/K is the Unit for the device program.
Script/S is a switch for the connectscript.
CloseWin/S is a switch for the Ctrl-D function.
CloseC/S is a switch for the Ctrl-C function.
FirstBreak/N/K is the time to wait for the first breaksignal when shutdown.
ContBreak/N/K is the time to wait between each signal. If =0 only one signal will be sent.
BreakC/S and BreakD/S is the signals to send.
CmdFrom/K can be one of PASSWD, PASSWD1 or COMMAND.
Allow can be one of ALWAYS, IFSTAR or USERFILE
UserFile/K is the userfile.

but it's recomended to use the prefsprogram.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage" "How do I use it?"

  If you want to use it local, you have to get a telnetapplication
like Amtelnet or Amitcp-telnet. When you open connection to localhost
you will se a logwindow opening by the same time (if you have selected
one). This window has to functions, one is to se what the user does
and you can also kick them out of your computer by pressing Ctrl-C. The
connection will shutdown and VCON will try to close. Also Ctrl-D will be
recieved thru this window to switch the log windows on and off.
  It's not always that VCON can close. When a program is using the file-
handle that VCON has created, it has to stay open, else the program would
crash. VCON will send one break signals to the program and send EOF
evrytime the program asks for a char. 
  After the windows has opened, go back to the telnet program and type
your login and pasword. If everything works, you will see the AmigaDOS
prompt. If it doesn't, send me an email and explain as much as you can.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "faq" "Frequently asked quistions"

I can only use VCON with the NOLOGIN option.

There could be many reasons.
Have you installed the loginsystem (multiuser or usergroup). Does the login
program that comes with the loginsystem work. Some people have problems to
add users to Miami, so I will explain easily how to add users. Go to the
Database - Users window in Miami. Press The Add button. In the "User name"
field type the login name you want to use. Also enter a password. The "User Id"
can be any number. "Group Id" can be any number too. "Real name" is the place
where you enter your "Real name". "Home dir" is the home directory for that
users, SYS: will work. And finally the "Shell" textfield. A working argument
would be "newcli *". VCON has to be set to usergroup login system if you want to 
use it with Miami. I hope this will help alot of people.

How to get rid of the "New shell process xxx" line ?

It is not VCON that prints the line, it is the newcli command that is started
by VCON. A sollution could be to use the shell program that comes with VCON
in the Extras drawer. Copy the program to the C: drawer, then change the
Shell entry in the passwdfile or Miami to "Shell S:Shell-startup" or
"Shell S:Remote-startup"

When I use ircii whith VCON it hangs.

This is a problem that I haven´t solved yet, I hope I will some day.

More and less doesn´t work with VCON.

Yes , I know this is becays they use the ACTION_DISKINFO packet
and is used to recieve info about the window that is connected to the
console and VCON doesn´t use any console, so...



@ENDNODE

@NODE "history" "The history of VCON"

@{b}Ver 0.4    9 September 1998.@{UB}
   Possibility to select where to get the Commans stated after login.
   Userfile where you can enter which users that have acces to telnet.
   Sends IAC codes that tells the client that VCON wont echo,
    but stull IAC isn´t supported.
   The shell entry in the passwd file can be used without the leading
    ´*´, this is becaus some other programs that read from that file
    doesn´t like it.
 
@{b}Ver 0.3    14 August 1998.@{UB}
   Exec device support with connectscript.                                             
   Can be started without inetd.                                                       
   Sends many breaksignals all the time if the user closes the connection.             
   Possibility to close log window.                                                    
   Fixed a bug in ACTION_READ.                                                         
   VCON sends 0 instead if -1 when EOF, some more programs work now.                   
   Arguments can be added direct to the command line (or inte the inetd.conf or miami).

@{b}Ver 0.2    12 April 1998.@{UB}
   Now Ctrl-Return (Ascii-10) works.
   Telnetprograms that send both ascii 13 and 10 work too.
   Removed a bug caused when using ACTION_DISK_INFO,
    now it send DOSFALSE instead of trash.
   Reads more than one character at a time.

@{B}Ver 0.1    11 April 1998.@{UB}
   This was the first version.
         
@ENDNODE

