@NODE "extras" "bonus"

The MUP program is a little clone from my Texas Instruments calculator.
I started to write it on boring lessons, but after a while it was so
fun so I sat some time at home in front of my litte texas and developed
it. Today there are versions for TI-82 (Texas), Amiga (!), Linux and even
the MSDOS. The source also comes with. The only reason why I let it come
with VCON is becaus you can run it remotly over VCON!.

The Shell program is just a little hack that starts a shell without leaving
the controll back to the console, it also skips to print the "New Shell
Process xxx". Ofcourde the source comes with.

But the biggest bonus of all is that VCON is free!!

@ENDNODE
 
